  m_Name: Pes_Middle_Phalanx_D1_R
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Pes_Middle_Phalanx_D1_R
  partName: Pes Middle Phalanx D1 Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The right middle phalanx of the first hind digit forms the intermediate segment
    of the toe between the proximal and distal phalanges. This bone contributes to
    flexibility, digital movement, and coordinated hindpaw mechanics during locomotion.
    Tendons and ligaments attached to the middle phalanx allow controlled flexion
  - and extension necessary for stable toe positioning and balanced movement. Although
    the first digit bears less weight than central digits, it still assists with
    traction and maneuverability. Proper structural health is important for smooth
    toe function and hindpaw coordination.
